CatDescriptText: Cutline of images published in the Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 2, 1955, pg. 12 reads: "Teen-Queen Contestants - These fourteen young misses of the Hill District are vying for the title Teen-Queen in the annual contest sponsored by Hill City.  They are, left to right:...Lois Tolliver and Gloria Evans"
TitMainTitle: Two frames: Portrait of Lois Tolliver wearing light colored sweater and circular medallion, posed in front of light colored background for Hill City Teen Queen contest; Portrait of Gloria Evans wearing light colored sweater with dark collar and scarf, posed in front of light colored background for Hill City Teen Queen contest
